The emails that resulted in the firings of two police officers and a court clerk in the city of Ferguson were released on Thursday  . 
  Police captain Richard Henke and city clerk Mary Ann Twitty were fired after exchanging racist emails . 
  In one email Henke said of President Obama; 'What black man holds a steady job for four years?' In the other emails President Obama is labelled a monkey and welfare recipients are described as 'lazy' and unable to speak English . 
  First Lady Michelle Obama is called a tribeswoman . 
  Former police sergeant William Mudd said he was getting his dogs welfare in one email . 
  All three were removed from their jobs after the emails were released . 
 